{
  "text": "EGFR mutation of NSCLCs was predominantly observed among Asian population, as well as females and non-smokers [CITATION_1] . Hsu CH et al. [CITATION_2] also performed a study in 2016, utilizing National Taiwan Lung Cancer Registry, and noticed EGFR mutation prevalence higher than 50%. Our study revealed a consistently high prevalence of EGFR mutation. Within this subgroup, females and non-smokers were predominant, as well as better differentiation of lung tumors.",
